'''Ayoube Amaimouni-Echghouyabe''' ({{Langx|ar|أيوب الميموني}}; born 30 November 2004) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]] for German {{German football updater|EinFrank}} club [[Eintracht Frankfurt]]. Born in Spain, he plays for the [[Morocco national football team|Morocco national team]].

==Early life==
Amaimouni-Echghouyabe was born on 30 November 2004 and is of [[Morocco|Moroccan]] descent through his parents.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.reviersport.de/fussball/3liga/a620191---3-liga-rwe-dsc-wollten-ihn-mehr-dieses-hoffenheimer-juwel-weg-oben.html|title=RWE und DSC wollten ihn nicht mehr - dieses Hoffenheimer Juwel ist auf dem Weg nach oben|trans-title=RWE and DSC no longer wanted him - this Hoffenheim gem is on his way to the top|language=de|publisher={{ill|RevierSport|de}}|date=1 October 2025|access-date=8 January 2026}}</ref> Born in [[Vic, Spain|Vic]], Spain, he grew up in the city.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.eintracht.de/news/der-stufenspringer-ayoube-amaimouni-echghouyab-174605?utm_source=google_organic|title=The Climber|trans-title=|language=en|publisher=[[Eintracht Frankfurt]]|date=3 January 2026|access-date=8 January 2026}}</ref>

==Club career==
As a youth player, Amaimouni joined the [[youth academy]] of Spanish side CF Voltregà. Following his stint there, he joined the youth academy of German side {{ill|TuS Eving-Lindenhorst|de}}. Subsequently, he joined the youth academy of German side [[Rot-Weiss Essen]]. Ahead of the [[2021–22 Arminia Bielefeld season|2021–22 season]], he joined the youth academy of German [[Bundesliga]] side [[Arminia Bielefeld]].

Two years later, he signed for German side [[SpVgg Erkenschwick]], where he made thirty league appearances and scored eighteen goals. During the summer of 2024, he signed for German side [[TSG 1899 Hoffenheim II]], where he made forty-six league appearances and scored sixteen goals.

On 2 January 2026, he signed a five-and-a-half-year contract with German [[Bundesliga]] side [[Eintracht Frankfurt]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Eintracht Frankfurt|url=https://en.eintracht.de/news/eintracht-verpflichtet-ayoube-amaimouni-echghouyab-174587|title=Eintracht sign Ayoube Amaimouni-Echghouyab|date=2 January 2026|access-date=8 January 2026}}</ref>

==International career==
On 26 May 2026, Amaimouni was named in [[Morocco national football team|Morocco]]'s 26-man squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://frmf.ma/fr/articles/coupe-du-monde-2026-de-la-fifa-coach-ouahbi-retient-26-joueurs-liste-finale |title=Coupe du Monde-2026 de la FIFA: coach Ouahbi retient 26 joueurs (liste finale) |trans-title=2026 FIFA World Cup: Coach Ouahbi names 26-man squad (final list) |publisher=[[Royal Moroccan Football Federation]] |date=26 May 2026 |access-date=26 May 2026 |language=fr}}</ref>

